    "question": "What is the main idea of the Potential Method in amortized analysis?",
    "answer": "The Potential Method maintains credit as potential energy associated with the data structure as a whole, helping analyze the average cost of operations. The cost of each operation is then determined by T(n)n."
  },
  {
    "question": "How does the Accounting Method analyze the cost of operations in amortized analysis?",
    "answer": "The Accounting Method assigns specific charges to each operation to account for future expensive operations, thereby spreading out the cost and analyzing it over a sequence of operations."
  }
