2025-05-27 09:57:54,442 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: Problems with polynomial time complexity, i.e., algorithms with time complexity of the form O(nk), where k is a constant and n is the size of the input.
2025-05-27 09:57:54,442 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,443 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 2:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,443 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What are Intractable problems?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,443 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: Problems with exponential time complexities, requiring high time for execution.
2025-05-27 09:57:54,444 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,444 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 3:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,444 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is a Decision problem?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,445 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: A problem for which the answer is yes or no, e.g., given a graph G, is there a coloring using at most k colors so that no two adjacent vertices have the same color?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,445 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,445 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 4:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,445 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is an Optimization problem?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,445 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: A problem that asks for the optimization of some measure, e.g., find the minimum number of colors required to color a graph such that no two adjacent vertices have the same color.
2025-05-27 09:57:54,445 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,445 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 5:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,445 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is Nondeterminism?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,445 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: A model where algorithms can guess correct solutions using functions like Guess(), Success(), and Failure().
2025-05-27 09:57:54,445 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,445 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 6:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,447 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is the P-class of decision problems?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,447 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: A decision problem belongs to P-class if a deterministic algorithm for its solution runs in polynomial time.
2025-05-27 09:57:54,447 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,447 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 7:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,447 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is the NP-class of decision problems?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,448 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: A decision problem belongs to NP-class if a nondeterministic algorithm for its solution runs in polynomial time.
2025-05-27 09:57:54,448 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,448 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 8:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,448 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is Satisfiability problem?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,448 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: Given a Boolean formula in Conjunctive Normal Form (CNF), determine if there exists an assignment of values to variables that makes the formula evaluate to True.
2025-05-27 09:57:54,449 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,449 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 9:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,449 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is Polynomial Reduction?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,449 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: Transforming one problem (L1) into another (L2) using a function T, where the answer to L1 can be derived from the answer to L2 in polynomial time.
2025-05-27 09:57:54,449 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,450 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 10:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,450 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is an NP-complete problem?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,450 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: A problem that is in NP and to which every problem in NP can be polynomially reduced.
2025-05-27 09:57:54,450 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,450 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 11:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,450 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is an NP-hard problem?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,451 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: A problem to which every problem in NP can be polynomially reduced, but it may not be in NP itself.
2025-05-27 09:57:54,452 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,452 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 12:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,453 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is an Approximation Algorithm?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,453 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: An algorithm that finds a solution close to the optimal solution in polynomial time, often used for NP-hard optimization problems.
2025-05-27 09:57:54,453 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,454 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
Flashcard 13:
2025-05-27 09:57:54,454 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is a Vertex Cover?
2025-05-27 09:57:54,454 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: A subset of vertices in a graph such that every edge has at least one endpoint in the subset.
2025-05-27 09:57:54,454 - services.copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-27 09:57:54,455 - services.copilot_service - INFO - 
