2025-05-29 23:54:35,901 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: The Aggregate Method calculates the total worst-case time for a sequence of *n* operations, denoted as *T(n)*, and then determines the amortized cost per operation as *T(n)/n*. This method applies even when the sequence includes multiple types of operations.
