Flashcard 4:
2025-05-29 23:54:35,902 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Question: Explain the Accounting Method in amortized analysis.
2025-05-29 23:54:35,902 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: The Accounting Method assigns an amortized cost to each operation, ensuring the sum of amortized costs is at least the sum of actual costs. If an operation's amortized cost exceeds its actual cost, the difference is stored as credit. If the actual cost exceeds the amortized cost, stored credits are used to cover the difference.
