2025-05-29 23:54:35,912 - services.copilot_service - INFO - Answer: Amortized analysis averages the cost of operations over a sequence, even if individual operations have different costs. For example, in heap sort, while inserting into a heap takes *O(log n)* time, amortized analysis considers the average cost across all insertions, often leading to a more accurate total time estimate than worst-case analysis.
